# Testing Strategy Defaults

Use this rule when planning or implementing tests.

## Framework and markers

- Use `pytest` as the default framework.
- Tests run through FreeCAD AppRun via `run_tests.py`, using the real PySide2 runtime.
- Follow marker taxonomy defined in `pyproject.toml`: `unit`, `integration`, `runtime_parity`, `manual_acceptance`.
- Use `unittest.mock` only for unit-level isolation boundaries.

## Layering expectations

- Start with fast unit tests for business logic and explicit contracts.
- Add integration tests for editor/runner boundaries, subprocess lifecycle, stdout/stderr, exit codes, and run logs.
- Keep broad UI workflow validation manual through `docs/ACCEPTANCE_TESTS.md` unless the user explicitly requests UI automation.

## Runtime compatibility

- All tests run inside the FreeCAD AppRun Python (3.11) with real PySide2.
- Any test tied to FreeCAD AppRun behavior should be marked `runtime_parity`.
- Runtime-parity tests should fail with actionable diagnostics or skip clearly when prerequisites are missing.

## Scope discipline

- During setup-only requests, scaffold config/docs/directories without writing speculative test cases.
